  "text": "set-6, which encodes one of the SET-domain-containing proteins in Neurospora (2), was induced ϳ80-fold by dsRNA. SET domains are a signature of lysine protein methyltransferases and are found in histone methyltransferases. In Neurospora, DIM-5, a SET-domain-containing protein, is a histone H3 Lys9 histone methyltransferase [CITATION_1] . Although the function of set-6 is not known, its strong induction by dsRNA suggests that it may have a role in chromatin remodeling in response to dsRNA expression.",
